         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[June 1855] ¶ My dear Mr Bateman ¶  ¶ It is a source of regret to me to be deprived of the pleasure of seeing you on my humble place, ¶  as I am urged by business to get to town. I have to thank you f...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">55.06.00a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward La Trobe Bateman</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">[June 1855]<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition</seg>. M went to Sydney at the beginning of July 1855 before the North Australian Exploring Expedition, visiting Melbourne again briefly in January 1857 before returning to Sydney to pack up specimens to send to Kew.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Mr Bateman</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is a source of regret to me to be deprived of the pleasure of seeing you on my humble place,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to E. Bateman, June 1855 (first letter).</p>
               </note> as I am urged by business to get to town. I have to thank you for the trouble which you have given you, in order to promote my views, and I am also deeply obliged both to Mrs Cobham and Mrs M'Crae. I shall write from Sydney and state about my proceedings, and I assure you, that I never shall forget the kindness of my friends</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr Bateman.</p>
         </div>
